{
  "model": "blog.post",
  "pk": 13,
  "fields": {
    "title": "Brownie",
    "slug": "brownie",
    "author": 1,
    "body": "📝 Ingredients\r\n\r\n1/2 cup (115g) butter\r\n\r\n1 cup (200g) sugar\r\n\r\n2 large eggs\r\n\r\n1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n\r\n1/3 cup (40g) unsweetened cocoa powder\r\n\r\n1/2 cup (65g) all-purpose flour\r\n\r\n1/4 tsp salt\r\n\r\n1/4 tsp baking powder\r\n\r\nOptional: 1/2 cup chocolate chips or chopped nuts\r\n\r\n👩‍🍳 Instructions\r\n\r\nPreheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease or line an 8×8-inch pan with parchment paper.\r\n\r\nMelt butter in a saucepan or microwave.\r\n\r\nMix in sugar, then add eggs and vanilla. Beat well until smooth.\r\n\r\nStir in cocoa powder, flour, salt, and baking powder until just combined.\r\n\r\nFold in chocolate chips or nuts if using.\r\n\r\nPour into pan and spread evenly.\r\n\r\nBake 20–25 minutes.\r\n\r\nFor fudgy brownies: bake closer to 20 minutes.\r\n\r\nFor cakier brownies: bake closer to 25 minutes.\r\n\r\nLet cool before cutting (this helps them set!).",
    "publish": "2026-03-19T04:50:19Z",
    "created": "2026-03-19T04:51:26.221Z",
    "updated": "2026-03-19T04:51:26.221Z",
    "status": "PB"
  }
},
{
  "model": "blog.post",
  "pk": 14,
  "fields": {
    "title": "Stuffed Aaloo paratha",
    "slug": "stuffed-aaloo-paratha",
    "author": 1,
    "body": "Among all stuffed parathas, aloo paratha is often the most loved. In my home, Aloo Paratha and Gobi Paratha are made quite often.\r\n\r\nThis aloo paratha recipe comes from my Punjabi mother-in-law and is one of the first parathas I learned to make. Like many Punjabi families, we usually roast the parathas with ghee and serve them with homemade butter (makhan).\r\n\r\nIf you prefer a lighter option, you can roast the parathas with oil and serve them with plain curd instead of butter. They still taste very good.\r\n\r\nIn this post, I also share two easy methods of rolling and stuffing the parathas. Once you understand the process, making aloo paratha at home becomes simple.\r\n\r\nTo make aloo paratha, you need two main components:\r\n\r\n1: Whole wheat dough: A soft dough made with whole wheat flour (atta), salt, oil and water. The dough is easy to knead by hand or in a stand mixer. Use Indian atta, which is finely ground whole wheat flour.\r\n\r\n2: Potato stuffing: Potatoes are boiled, peeled and mashed. The mashed potatoes are mixed with herbs, spices and salt.\r\n\r\nThe dough is rolled into small discs, the spiced, tangy potato filling is placed inside and sealed. The stuffed dough is then rolled again and roasted on a hot tawa with ghee or oil until golden and crisp.\r\n\r\nMore Punjabi-style Parathas To Try!",
    "publish": "2026-04-01T11:13:28Z",
    "created": "2026-04-01T11:16:30.806Z",
    "updated": "2026-04-01T11:16:30.806Z",
    "status": "PB"
  }
},
